Rating: 3
I loved the idea of these combination of flavors, but had a few issues with the recipe. First off, to brown mushrooms it's extremely important that you do not crowd them in the saute pan. Otherwise, they will sweat too quickly, get liquidy, and then steam instead of browning. Make sure you have very large pan or use multiple pans, or brown in batches. Secondly, my shallots became horribly bitter, so I ended up not using them. It seems they need to be cooked at a lower heat and not browned too much. Other than that, this was good and made a great Thanksgiving side.

