Fabulous as is. I thought this was extremely easy and straightforward, even frying the shallots. I used a small, 7" skillet, which made the oil layer deeper. It wasn't time-consuming to look over into the skillet, give it a shake, every couple of minutes, while I was doing something else. Very likely, that step could be done later, closer to serving or recrisped in the oven. Most important, IMO, there's no way you should be adding any liquid to the brussels sprouts while they're roasting. If you do, you might as well boil or steam them. The browned bits are leaves are integral to roasted veg. Don't be afraid of them or think they're ruined as a result. I loved the browned parts and couldn't stop nibbling on them. Definitely something to make again with different mushroom combinations. This time I used shitake and crimini.

