Rating: 4
Brussel sprouts have been controversial in my house for years. I love them and everyone else hates them. This recipe changed my husbands mind and kind of changed my children's minds. I do recommend a few changes. 450 degrees for 35 minutes is is too hot and too long to cook the brussel sprouts. The leaves burn and re bitter. Reduce the heart to about 375 degrees, stir frequently, and cook about 25 minutes depending on the size of your sprouts. Sautee the shallots in olive oil and add the garlic to the shallots instead of the sprouts to reduce burning. Carmelize the onions and garlic together. Cook the mushrooms in half olive oil and half butter, instead of all butter. Delicious!

