Rating: 4
This is one fabulous brussels sprouts recipe. I made it for Christmas dinner and even those clamining to hate brussels sprouts liked this dish. Based on other warnings of the sprouts burning in the oven, I modified the recipe a bit cooked the brussels sprouts cut-side down on a sheet pan (still oiled and seasoned per recipe) at the recommended temperature. Once the sprouts browned, I reduced the temperature by 50 degrees and poured water into the pan, just to cover the bottom of the sprouts, and let them cook / steam until tender. This gave a tender sprout that wasn't dreid or burned. Making the shallots a day ahead of time was no problem. They also make a yummy addition to a salad topped with a creamy dressing. I used baby bellas instead of mixed wild mushrooms. Couldn't really justify the price of wild mushrooms in this case. I will certainly make this again.

